==English==
===Etymology===

From {{L.}} ''ascites'', borrowed from {{Gr.}} [[ἀσκιτής]], from [[ἀσκός]], "wineskin."



===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#{{medicine}} An accumulation of fluid in the peritoneal cavity, frequently symptomatic of liver disease.

